# useful_dotfiles

What in `notes2/_archive/` is genuinely useful for the dotfiles repo and is
NOT already present there. Generated by comparing `_archive/` against
`~/data/repos/dotfiles` (branch feat/copyq).

Legend:  [ADD] worth adding  ·  [OPTIONAL] niche/personal  ·  [SKIP] superseded/covered


## [ADD] Worth pulling into dotfiles

### nano config  →  dotfiles/dot_nanorc
Source: _archive/bashes/.nanorc
The dotfiles repo has NO nano configuration (it ships dot_inputrc and
dot_screenrc but nothing for nano). This one is generic and useful:
  set tabsize 4 / tabstospaces, historylog, casesensitive, smooth, morespace
  include "/usr/share/nano/nanorc.nanorc"  (syntax highlighting)
Action: copy to dotfiles as `dot_nanorc` (→ ~/.nanorc).

### git large-object finder  →  dotfiles/dot_scripts/
Source: _archive/scripts/gitlistobjectsbysize.sh
Lists every blob across all commits sorted by size — the standard tool for
finding what bloated a repo before a gc/filter-repo. Nothing equivalent exists
in dot_scripts or dot_bash_git.
Action: copy to dot_scripts/gitlistobjectsbysize.sh.


## [OPTIONAL] Niche — add only if you still use the app

### Firefox bookmark-folder colors  →  userChrome.css
Source: _archive/scripts/userChrome.css
Colors bookmark folders in the Firefox sidebar/toolbar. Only relevant if you
use Firefox AND enable toolkit.legacyUserProfileCustomizations.stylesheets.
Would live at ~/.mozilla/firefox/<profile>/chrome/userChrome.css — the profile
path is dynamic, so it doesn't map cleanly to chezmoi. Keep as reference.

### Server / container hardening templates
Source: _archive/scripts/golden-image/  (CIS.conf, motd, issue, unit8-ubuntu.list, Dockerfile)
A login banner (issue), MOTD, CIS sysctl hardening and an APT source list for a
"golden image". These are SERVER/CI build artifacts, not personal dotfiles —
useful as a reference if you build hardened base images, but they don't belong
in chezmoi. Note the banner text still references a former employer; scrub
before reuse.

### WSL bootstrap scripts
Source: _archive/wsl-setup/home-skel/scripts/  (binenv-install.sh, podman-install.sh, wsl-*.sh)
Only relevant on WSL. dotfiles already installs podman (dot_scripts/installpodman.sh)
and references binenv (dot_bash_joco). Pull binenv-install.sh only if you want a
standalone installer; otherwise skip.


## [SKIP] Already covered or superseded — do NOT add

- dotfiles/bash-extras — every reusable alias/function is ALREADY in the repo:
    extract()      → dot_bash_aliases
    ref/refresh, dua, lt, rmduplicates, screen_set_window_title → dot_bash_joco
    gsize          → dot_bash_git
    kns/ks/kex kubeconfig switchers → dot_bash_kubectl
  Nothing unique remains.
- dotfiles/bashkube — kube aliases; superseded by dot_bash_kubectl.
- scripts/redshift.config — superseded by KDE Night Color (managed in dot_config/kwinrc).
- new-install-ubuntu/keybindings/* (*_plasma_keys, custom_*, xfce4-*.xml)
  — old Plasma/XFCE shortcut dumps; current shortcuts live in
    dot_config/kglobalshortcutsrc + khotkeysrc.
- new-install-ubuntu/customkeys/ (customkeys.py + .service) — custom key remapper;
  superseded by keyd (dot_scripts/wayland_navigate_keys.sh).
- scripts/cpu_temp_xfce.sh — XFCE genmon; you're on Plasma + Prometheus/Grafana.
- scripts/*.sh GUI snippets (copyq_toggle, maximize/minimize_window, xclip_shortcut,
  reload_bashrc, youtube_mp3, fn_on, keyb) — already ported/consolidated into
  dot_scripts (window.sh, paste_snippet.sh, lib/gui-session.sh) earlier.
- bashes/ (.bashrc, .bash_aliases, .tmux.conf, .gitconfig, .profile, .xsession,
  .wakatime.cfg, raspberry_bashrc, etc.) — old machine dotfiles; superseded by the
  current dot_bashrc / dot_tmux.conf / dot_gitconfig.tmpl / dot_zshrc.
- sim/ (.bash_aliases_sim, .nanorc_sim, .tmux.conf_sim) — sim-machine variants.
- dotfiles/myhotkeys.ahk, scripts/ahk/* — Windows AutoHotkey, not Linux.
- dotfiles/win*.sh, wsl-Dockerfile, Makefile(_ai) — dead project / Windows / WSL build.
- scripts/install_* / opencv_* / ubuntu_fresh_install / atom_* / cuda_* — obsolete
  Ubuntu installers; dotfiles uses Ansible (playbook.yml + packages.yml).
- drafts/, helldivers/, tinder/, playground/, *email*.sh, job_reply_*.sh,
  kind_regards_paste.sh — personal/scratch/game/job macros.


## Summary
Only TWO items are clear additions: `dot_nanorc` and the git large-object
finder script. Everything else in _archive is already in dotfiles, superseded
by the current KDE/keyd/Ansible setup, or personal/project scratch.
